 &lt;p&gt;Why use Cricket Wireless?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;  Cricket Wireless uses AT&amp;amp;T cell towers so it will have native AT&amp;amp;T coverage plus some domestic roaming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;  You can even have Canada and Mexico roaming coverage when traveling by paying $10 more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;  Cricket Wireless get new feature even faster than AT&amp;amp;T&amp;#x2019;s prepaid plan (former AT&amp;amp;T gophone). For example, Cricket Wireless user have VoLTE (Voice over LTE) now while AT&amp;amp;T&amp;#x2019;s prepaid plan still missing that option.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;  Tax is included. Why pay 20% more tax?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;  Affordable family plan, 5 lines for $100! No hidden fee.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;  Local stores everywhere if you need assistence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;  Cricket Wireless offer more GB than other competitors in same price.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The only downside is Cricket Wireless limit the max LTE peak download speeds to 8 Mbps, however, that is fast enough to watch HD video. If you&amp;#x2019;re a new customer looking to try Cricket Wireless and want to save even more, you can use our&amp;#xA0; referral for a $25 Credit for each line. If you&amp;#x2019;re planning on moving multiple lines, after you activate your own line, then refer your other lines so you receive your own $25 credit for each line! After you have them all transferred, you should be able to group them all together for some major group discounts by calling customer service. &lt;/p&gt;
